      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The avalanche risk above 1800 m increases from moderate to considerable during the daytime changes. Below that, it is low in the morning and moderate later on. With sunshine, wet snow in combination with persistent weak layers becomes a problem. Particularly in extremely steep terrain, wet loose snow and slab avalanches release by themselves or with little additional load. Wet soft and slab avalanches reach medium size.\n\nOn steep slopes with smooth ground that have not yet been discharged, wet, medium-sized gliding avalanches can also occur at any time in all aspects.",
        "highlights": "Weak layers become reactive with moisture penetration."
      },
